  13:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   ==============================================================================
  14:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  15:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   ==============================================================================   
  16:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       [..] The LCD HAL driver can be used as follow:
  17:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****     
  18:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) Declare a LCD_HandleTypeDef handle structure.
  19:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  20:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) Prepare the initialization of the LCD low level resources by implementing your HAL_LCD_Ms
  21:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           (##) Enable the LCDCLK (same as RTCCLK): to configure the RTCCLK/LCDCLK, use the RCC func
  22:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****                HAL_RCCEx_PeriphCLKConfig, indicating here RCC_PERIPHCLK_LCD and the selected clock 
  23:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****                source (HSE, LSI or LSE)
  24:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           (##) The frequency generator allows you to achieve various LCD frame rates starting from 
  25:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****                LCD input clock frequency (LCDCLK) which can vary from 32 kHz up to 1 MHz.
  26:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           (##) LCD pins configuration:
  27:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****               - Enable the clock for the LCD GPIOs
  28:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****               - Configure these LCD pins as alternate function no-pull.
  29:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           (##) Enable the LCD interface clock.
  30:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  31:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) Set the Prescaler, Divider, Blink mode, Blink Frequency Duty, Bias, Voltage Source, 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Tilen\AppData\Local\Temp\ccpoirSe.s 			page 2


  32:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           Dead Time, Pulse On Duration and Contrast in the hlcd Init structure.
  33:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  34:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) Initialize the LCD registers by calling the HAL_LCD_Init() API.
  35:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           (##) The HAL_LCD_Init() API configures the low level Hardware (GPIO, CLOCK, ...etc)
  36:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****                by calling the user customized HAL_LCD_MspInit() API.
  37:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) After calling the HAL_LCD_Init() the LCD RAM memory is cleared
  38:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  39:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) Optionally you can update the LCD configuration using these macros:
  40:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****            (##) LCD High Drive using the __HAL_LCD_HIGHDRIVER_ENABLE() and __HAL_LCD_HIGHDRIVER_DIS
  41:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****            (##) LCD Pulse ON Duration using the __HAL_LCD_PULSEONDURATION_CONFIG() macro
  42:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****            (##) LCD Dead Time using the __HAL_LCD_DEADTIME_CONFIG() macro  
  43:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****            (##) The LCD Blink mode and frequency using the __HAL_LCD_BLINK_CONFIG() macro
  44:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****            (##) The LCD Contrast using the __HAL_LCD_CONTRAST_CONFIG() macro  
  45:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  46:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) Write to the LCD RAM memory using the HAL_LCD_Write() API, this API can be called
  47:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           several times to update the different LCD RAM registers before calling 
  48:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           HAL_LCD_UpdateDisplayRequest() API.
  49:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  50:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) The HAL_LCD_Clear() API can be used to clear the LCD RAM memory.
  51:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  52:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       (#) When the LCD RAM memory is updated, enable the update display request calling
  53:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****           the HAL_LCD_UpdateDisplayRequest() API.
  54:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  55:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       [..] LCD and low power modes: The LCD remain active during STOP mode.
  56:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** 
  57:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   @endverbatim
