 317:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** /** @addtogroup LCD_Exported_Functions_Group2
 318:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *  @brief LCD RAM functions 
 319:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *
 320:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** @verbatim   
 321:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  ===============================================================================
 322:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****                       ##### IO operation functions #####
 323:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  ===============================================================================  
 324:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  [..] Using its double buffer memory the LCD controller ensures the coherency of the 
 325:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  displayed information without having to use interrupts to control LCD_RAM 
 326:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  modification.
 327:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  The application software can access the first buffer level (LCD_RAM) through 
 328:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  the APB interface. Once it has modified the LCD_RAM using the HAL_LCD_Write() API,
 329:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  it sets the UDR flag in the LCD_SR register using the HAL_LCD_UpdateDisplayRequest() API.
 330:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  This UDR flag (update display request) requests the updated information to be 
 331:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  moved into the second buffer level (LCD_DISPLAY).
 332:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  This operation is done synchronously with the frame (at the beginning of the 
 333:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  next frame), until the update is completed, the LCD_RAM is write protected and 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Tilen\AppData\Local\Temp\ccpoirSe.s 			page 8


 334:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  the UDR flag stays high.
 335:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  Once the update is completed another flag (UDD - Update Display Done) is set and
 336:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  generates an interrupt if the UDDIE bit in the LCD_FCR register is set.
 337:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  The time it takes to update LCD_DISPLAY is, in the worst case, one odd and one 
 338:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  even frame.
 339:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  The update will not occur (UDR = 1 and UDD = 0) until the display is 
 340:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****  enabled (LCDEN = 1).
 341:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****       
 342:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c **** @endverbatim
 343:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   * @{
 344:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   */
