 470:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   * @note   Each time software modifies the LCD_RAM it must set the UDR bit to 
 471:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         transfer the updated data to the second level buffer. 
 472:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         The UDR bit stays set until the end of the update and during this 
 473:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         time the LCD_RAM is write protected. 
 474:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   * @note   When the display is disabled, the update is performed for all 
 475:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         LCD_DISPLAY locations.
 476:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         When the display is enabled, the update is performed only for locations 
 477:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         for which commons are active (depending on DUTY). For example if 
 478:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   *         DUTY = 1/2, only the LCD_DISPLAY of COM0 and COM1 will be updated.    
 479:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   * @retval None
 480:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_lcd.c ****   */
